#The Identifier
		1) correct name: -letters
						 -numbers
						  -_
						  -$
						   -no number at first
						    -no keywords


		2) self-documenting: -avgNum
							-camelcase
							 *class: XxxXxx
						 	*var; xxxXxx
							*method: xxxXxx()


		3) consistency: calcScore(), calcAvg() v+n for method, adj+n for variable


	#Data Types
		-2 types

			-Primitive Data Types (basic data types java defined)

		-Integral  (int numbers and characters)
			*1 byte
			*2 short
			*2 char
			*4 int
			*8 long

		-Floating
			*4 float 		3.14f
			*8 double		3.14

		-Bolean

			#Data type conversion
				*Java only calculate one operation each time
					(3 + 5 * 2) / 3 -> 5 * 2
					*Java only calculate two values with the same data type
					3 + 3.14		coverted to    ->   3.0 + 3.14
					*int + int =int
					*double + double = double
					*char + char =int *** sprcial one, when calculate with char, char will always be converted to int.
					* int + char = int
					*int + double = double
					*float + double = double *** convert the less accurate one to more accurate one


		#Century and Decade
		year -> century and decade
			century: year / 100 + 1
			decade: year % 100 / 10 * 10